  {name:"Critical Values — Microbiology",abbr:"CRIT-MICRO",ref:"Positive results requiring urgent clinical action and documentation",
   up:["Positive blood culture — ALWAYS call immediately — specify organism and sensitivities","CSF any organism — meningitis — antibiotics within 30 minutes of decision","Positive malaria film/RDT — urgent treatment","MRSA in sterile site — contact precautions + notify infection control","C. difficile toxin positive — contact precautions immediately + stop offending antibiotics","AFB smear positive (TB) — respiratory isolation + public health notification","HIV positive (new diagnosis) — urgent linkage to HIV care"],
   dn:["Not applicable"],
   tip:"Blood culture Gram stain guide: Gram-positive cocci clusters = MRSA/MSSA → vancomycin (MRSA) or flucloxacillin (MSSA). Gram-positive cocci chains = Streptococcus/Enterococcus → benzylpenicillin or amoxicillin. Gram-negative rods = Enterobacteriaceae or Pseudomonas → pip-tazo or cefuroxime. Yeast = Candida → echinocandin (ICU). Staph. aureus bacteraemia: ALWAYS requires echocardiogram and minimum 14 days IV antibiotics (28 days if deep focus)."}
